Step 1: Create the .env file
The .env file wasn't created automatically. Create it from the example:
cp .env.example .env
Step 2: Run the setup script (recommended)
The setup script handles everything:
./setup.sh
This will:
Create a virtual environment
Install dependencies
Create the .env file (if missing)
Create necessary directories
Run database migrations
OR: Manual setup
If you prefer to do it manually:
# 1. Create virtual environmentpython3 -m venv venv# 2. Activate itsource venv/bin/activate# 3. Install dependenciespip install -r requirements.txt# 4. Create .env filecp .env.example .env# 5. Run migrationspython manage.py migrate# 6. Start the serverpython manage.py runserver
